    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-01-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-01-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="839"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d839">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 882.51/286.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-01-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 11, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Disquieting rumors have reached New York bankers of continued deterioration of
                    Liberian finances, concerning which a full and frank <pb facs="0784" n="668"
                        xml:id="pg_668"/> statement is necessary if the loan is not to be imperiled.
                    Mail to Department as full a statement as possible of receipts and expenditures
                    during last twelve months, especially as to what additions have been made to the
                    floating debt of Liberia certified on December 31, 1911.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
